President Obama and First Lady Michelle Obama sent warm wishes to those celebrating Kwanzaa, acknowledging the joyous time of year when African Americans and all Americans come together to celebrate cultural traditions. They emphasized the importance of reflecting on the past while embracing the promise of the future. The seven principles of Kwanzaa were highlighted, expressing values that inspire individuals, families, communities, and the country as a whole. Despite acknowledging the challenges faced by African American families and all communities, the Obamas expressed their belief in the spirit of perseverance and hope that exists within the community. They extended their prayers and best wishes for the holiday season and the upcoming year.